Code developed and tested under Ruby1.8.7;
If you need to Draw a performance monitoring diagram with Gruff, ruby1.8.6 is recommened.

Usage example:
> Perf_mon_runner.rb [MonitredIPs] [Duration(min)] [Interval(sec)] [FilePath]
such as:
> Perf_mon_runner.rb \"ip1,ip2,ip3\" 1 20 \"D:\\\\temp\\\\\"

Performance measurements include:
\\processor(_total)\\% processor time
\\processor(_total)\\% user time
\\processor(_total)\\% privileged time
\\Memory\\Available Kbytes
\\physicaldisk(_total)\\% disk read time
\\physicaldisk(_total)\\% disk write time
\\network interface(*#1)\\bytes total/sec